[Method]
AddColumns
[Prefix]
Odcl_Grid_
[Desc]
This method adds columns to a Grid control. Complete control of each column has been provided with this method, the width, justification, and optional image from the image list can or must be specified for each control. Because this method asks you to specify the insertion index, columns don't have to be added at the end, but if necessary can be added in the beginning or the middle of the existing columns. 
\par \par The column justification is to be set using:
\par 0	Left
\par 1	Center
\par 2	Right
\par \par \b Please Note:\b0 \par Because the Grid control was design exclusively for Internet Explorer, the justification for the first column will only display left justification.  We wish this design intent of Microsoft's was not so, but unfortunately this is how Microsoft provides the control.
\par \par \b Note:\b0 \par Create list as follows: \par 
          (List (List x y ...) (List x y ...) ...)
\par We have found ObjectARX does not always like lists created as follows:
\par          '(x y ...) (x y ...) ... 
\par \par \b Note:\b0 If the grid has columns added using the properties wizard, this function will not add any new columns.
[Arguments]
ProjectFileName
\par\tab 
[Begin List]
[Begin List]
\par\tab nColIndex
[as Integer]
\par\tab sColText
[as String]
\par\tab nJustification
[as Integer]
\par\tab nColWidth
[as Integer]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 nImageListIndex
[as Integer]
[End List]
\par\tab ...
[End List]


[Method]
AddRow
[Prefix]
Odcl_Grid_
[Desc]
This method adds a new item to the end of a Grid control and will also fill in the cells in the entire row according to how many columns have been setup. Using this method the very first cell under the first column can be specified to display an image from the image list. Use \cf1 Odcl_Grid_SetItemImage \cf0 to set the icons of any column cell.
\par \par \b Note:\b0 \par Create list as follows: \par 
          (List x y ...)
\par We have found ObjectARX does not always like lists created as follows:
\par          '(x y ...)
\par 
\par \b Also Note:\b0 The style of the cell or column only governs the behavior of the cell and what happens when the user clicks on the cell.
\par \par \b \b For example \b0\b0if you set the style 33 - Linetype Cell, the current selection for the linetype must be correctly set in the \cf2 Odcl_Grid_AddString \cf0 or \cf2 Odcl_Grid_AddRow \cf0 functions. The item may not be changed to correctly display one of the listed items.
[Arguments Return] as Integer
ProjectFileName
\par\tab 
[Begin List]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 nImageIndex ...
[as Integer]
\par\tab sText
[as String]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 sColText1 sColText2 sColText3 ...
[as String]
[End List]

[Method]
AddString
[Prefix]
Odcl_Grid_
[Desc]
This method adds a new row to the end of a Grid control and fills in each of the cells using a single string. 
The string is to have a separator that identifies what parts of the strings belong in which cell. 
If the sSeparator argument of this function is not specified, "\t" will be assumed.

\par \par \b1 Please note: \b0 This functions does not give you the ability to specify image icons to be display in any cell, the function \cf2 Odcl_Grid_SetItemImage \cf0 should be used after this function is called to assign image icons in the cells.
\par 
\par \b Also Note:\b0 The style of the cell or column only governs the behavior of the cell and what happens when the user clicks on the cell.
\par \par \b For example \b0if you set the style 33 - Linetype Cell, the current selection for the linetype must be correctly set in the \cf2 Odcl_Grid_AddString \cf0 or \cf2 Odcl_Grid_AddRow \cf0 functions. The item may not be changed to correctly display one of the listed items.
[Arguments Return] as Integer
ProjectFileName
\par\tab sString
[as String]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0  sSeparator
[as String]

[Method]
InsertString
[Prefix]
Odcl_Grid_
[Desc]
This method inserts a new row in the specified position of a Grid control and fills in each of the cells using a single string. 
The string is to have a separator that identifies what parts of the strings belong in which cell. 
If the sSeparator argument of this function is not specified, "\t" will be assumed.

\par \par \b1 Please note: \b0 This functions does not give you the ability to specify image icons to be display in any cell, the function \cf2 Odcl_Grid_SetItemImage \cf0 should be used after this function is called to assign image icons in the cells.
\par 
\par \b Also Note:\b0 The style of the cell or column only governs the behavior of the cell and what happens when the user clicks on the cell.
\par \par \b For example \b0if you set the style 33 - Linetype Cell, the current selection for the linetype must be correctly set in the \cf2 Odcl_Grid_AddString \cf0 or \cf2 Odcl_Grid_AddRow \cf0 functions. The item may not be changed to correctly display one of the listed items.
[Arguments Return] as Integer
ProjectFileName
\par\tab nIndex
[as Integer]
\par\tab sString
[as String]
\par\tab\i{Optional}\i0 sSeparator
[as String]


