[Method]
SortTextItems
[Prefix]
Odcl_Grid_
[Desc]
This method will sort the columns in ascending or descending order, based on the column index provided. This method will not keep track of which column was sorted as ascending or descending, this is up to you.
[Arguments]
ProjectFileName
\par\tab nColIndex
[as Integer]
\par\tab bAscending
[as Integer, T or Nil] (1 or T = Ascending, 0 or Nil = Descending) 


[Method]
SortNumericItems
[Prefix]
Odcl_Grid_
[Desc]
This method will sort the columns in ascending or descending order using a numeric comparison, based on the column index provided. This method will not keep track of which column was sorted as ascending or descending, this is up to you.
[Arguments]
ProjectFileName
\par\tab nColIndex
[as Integer]
\par\tab bAscending
[as Integer, T or Nil] (1 or T = Ascending, 0 or Nil = Descending) 




[Method]
ShowTextBox
[Prefix]
Odcl_Grid_
[Desc]
This method will activate a text box to edit a cell. 
The style argument accepts a numeric value that indicated the style of the text box to be used. The values are as shown below:
\par 
\par 	 6 - Strings	
\par 	 7 - AngleUnits	
\par 	 8 - Integers	
\par 	 9 - Units		
\par 	10 - UpperCase	
\par 	11 - LowerCase	
\par 	12 - Password	
\par 	13 - MultiLine	
\par 	14 - Currency	
\par 	15 - Date		
\par 	16 - Time		
\par 	17 - Percentage	
\par 
\par \b Note:\b0 If the style does not match the pre-assigned value for the cell or column, then the pre-assigned value will be used.
[Arguments]
ProjectFileName
\par\tab nRow
[as Integer]
\par\tab nCol
[as Integer]
\par\tab nStyle
[as Integer]


[Method]
ShowComboBox
[Prefix]
Odcl_Grid_
[Desc]
This method will activate a combo box to edit a cell. 
The style argument accepts a numeric value that indicated the style of the drop down list to be used. The values are as shown below:
\par 
\par 	18 - DropDown
\par 	19 - ArrowHeads
\par 	20 - Acad Colors
\par 	21 - TextStyle List
\par 	22 - PlotStyle Names
\par 	23 - PlotStyle Tables
\par 	24 - Plotter List	
\par 	25 - Fonts		
\par 	26 - Drive List
\par 	27 - Layer List	
\par 	28 - DimStyle List
\par 	36 - Strings Combo
\par 	37 - AngleUnits Combo
\par 	38 - Integers Combo
\par 	39 - Units Combo	
\par 	40 - UpperCase Combo
\par 	41 - LowerCase Combo
\par 
\par \b Note:\b0 If the style does not match the pre-assigned value for the cell or column, then the pre-assigned value will be used.
[Arguments]
ProjectFileName
\par\tab nRow
[as Integer]
\par\tab nCol
[as Integer]
\par\tab nStyle
[as Integer]
\par\tab [Begin List]
DropDownItem
[as String]
[End List]



[Method]
ShowImageComboBox
[Prefix]
Odcl_Grid_
[Desc]
This method will activate an image combo box to edit a cell. 
[Arguments]
